title: Excludes from the definition of "dealer" an economically sustainable transportation provider, as defined in section 223 of the elder law
summary: Excludes from the definition of "dealer" an economically sustainable transportation provider, as defined in section 223 of the elder law; defines economically sustainable transportation provider to mean a non-profit provider of transportation services that submits to the director and obtains approval of a plan demonstrating the provider is capable of providing economically sustainable transportation services.
actClause: AN ACT to amend the vehicle and traffic law, in relation to exempting, from the definition of "dealer", economically sustainable transportation providers
